        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(diagnostic): lower stall abort threshold and extend model-call recovery to CLI sessions",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThe diagnostic heartbeat detects stalled sessions (model calls stuck >120s) but the abort threshold was 360s (6 minutes) — far too long to recover from a hung provider. Additionally, `isStalledModelCallRecoveryEligible` required `hasActiveEmbeddedRun === true`, which excluded CLI harness sessions (e.g. Codex-backed providers) from model-call recovery entirely.\n\nThis fix:\n1. Lowers `MIN_STALLED_EMBEDDED_RUN_ABORT_MS` from 300s → 180s and the warn multiplier from 3× → 2×, so stuck model calls abort at ~240s instead of 360s\n2. Extends model-call recovery to CLI sessions where `hasActiveEmbeddedRun` is not set, using a 2× safety threshold (480s default) as a conservative guard\n\nFixes #94650\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Gateway diagnostic detected a 149s+ stalled model call but logged `recovery=none` without aborting. The abort threshold was 360s — unreachable for the stuck session.\n\n**Real setup tested**:\n- **Runtime**: OpenClaw test harness (vitest)\n- **Command**: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts`\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n```\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  70 passed (70)\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**:\n- Stalled embedded-run model calls will be aborted at ~240s (max(180000, 120000 * 2) = 240000ms) instead of 360s\n- Stalled CLI model calls (where `hasActiveEmbeddedRun` is not set) can now be recovered, with 480s default threshold (2× the abort threshold)\n\n**What was not tested**: Live hung model call with a real provider. The fix changes only thresholds and conditions; recovery execution path is unchanged.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- Existing diagnostic tests: 70/70 pass, no regression\n- One threshold test updated to reflect new default (300000 → 180000)\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`No` — only changes internal watchdog timing)\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`No` — users can still override via `diagnostics.stuckSessionAbortMs`)\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`No`)\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n- Lowering the abort threshold could cause premature aborts if model calls legitimately take 3+ minutes.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n- The 240s default is still very generous for modern API calls (most complete in 30-60s)\n- Operators with slow providers can set `diagnostics.stuckSessionAbortMs` higher\n- The 2× multiplier for CLI sessions adds extra safety margin\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n- Maintainer review\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-94650-gateway-watchdog-stall-recovery",
